<HEADLINE> Ethnic Violence Claims At Least 10 in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 10 (Xinhua) -- At least 10 people were
killed and many injured today in ethnic violence in Manipur,
northeastern India, the Press Trust of India reported.
</P>
<P>
According to official sources, armed persons raided four ethnic
Kuki villages in the northeastern Indian state in the early hours
this morning and set on fire more than 100 houses.
</P>
<P>
The assailants fired indiscriminately at fleeing villagers,
killing seven persons on the spot. Three others succumbed to their
injuries on the way to hospital.
</P>
<P>
The local police have launched a manhunt to track down the
killers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
