<HEADLINE> One Killed in Oil Refinery Explosion in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 10 (Xinhua) -- One man was killed and two
injured today in an explosion which took place in an oil refinery
in Reichstett, north of Strasbourg, Agence France-Presse (AFP)
quoted police as saying.
</P>
<P>
The explosion occurred when an oil tank truck was loading oil in
the refinery located near a road transport station. The driver of
the truck, Gilles Richter, was killed, said AFP.
</P>
<P>
Two other truckers who were also loading their oil tank trucks
nearby were injured.
</P>
<P>
Security men and firemen immediately put under control the fire
which resulted from the explosion, while the exact cause of the
explosion is not known immediately. 
</P>
</TEXT>
