<HEADLINE> Flavio Cotti Elected Swiss President for 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Flavio Cotti was today elected
the president of the Swiss confederation for the one-year term of
1998.
</P>
<P>
In a national assembly voting, Cotti, current Swiss foreign
minister, won 173 votes out of 192.
</P>
<P>
Cotti, now 58, entered the Swiss Federal Council (government)
in 1987. He was the Swiss president in 1991.
</P>
<P>
Ms Ruth Dreifuss, 58, was elected the vice president in the
voting in the Swiss capital of Bern.
</P>
<P>
Local press reports asserted that she would have a chance to
become the first female president of Switzerland in the future.
</P>
</TEXT>
