<HEADLINE> U.S. Shooting Suspect Takes Children Hostage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 10 (Xinhua) -- A shooting suspect broke
into a house in a chase by police and took two small children
hostage Tuesday in downtown Orlando, Florida, local media
reports said today.
</P>
<P>
John Edward Armstrong was suspected of shooting a man to death
earlier Tuesday in nearby Winter Park, north of Orlando. He
broke into the house after his car rammed another car while
fleeing police.
</P>
<P>
The career criminal, who was released early from armed robbery
charges in March, took the children, a 4-year-old and 2-year-old
girl, hostage but released two women when he got into the house.
</P>
<P>
Police have decided against using tear gas to force the
39-year-old Armstrong out of the residence for fear of harming the
children.
</P>
<P>
Hostage negotiators and Armstrong's family asked him to free
the children, but he has shown no indication that he is willing to
let them go.
</P>
<P>
Residents closest to the hostage scene were evacuated from
their homes and the area remained condoned off this morning.
</P>
</TEXT>
