<HEADLINE> Cook, UNSCOM Chairman Meet on Iraqi Arms Inspection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 10 (Xinhua) -- British Foreign Secretary Robin
Cook held talks here this afternoon with Richard Butler, Chairman
of the UN Special Commission (UNSCOM) on Iraq to exchange views on
the arms inspection in Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a joint press conference after the meeting, Cook
described the work of the UNSCOM in Iraq as a "vital job" and he
urged the Iraqi government to honor all UN resolutions concerned.
</P>
<P>
Cook stressed that Britain's Labor government is fully
committed to support the work of the UN arms inspection team in
Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Butler said that he would hold talks with Iraqi government
officials later this week over gaining access to all sites in
Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Butler noted that there was no question of Iraq being allowed
to ban the UN arms inspection team from investigating sites which
Baghdad considered to be sensitive.
</P>
<P>
"We can't work that way. We'll be talking about getting access
in a way which shows respect for Iraqi security," he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
