<HEADLINE> BT, ESB Form Joint Venture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 10 (Xinhua) - British Telecommunications (BT)
and the Republic of Ireland company Electricity Supply Board (ESB)
have reached agreement in principle to form a joint venture.
</P>
<P>
The new company will be a 50-50 joint venture. Investment by
the alliance will be approximately 75 million pounds (120 million
US dollars) in the first five years growing to 130 million pounds
(208 million US dollars) over ten years.
</P>
<P>
According to an announcement by BT here today, the company will
have more than 300 personnel.
</P>
<P>
The move is a part of BT's strategy in other European
countries, where it has formed an alliance with a local utility in
preparation for the full liberalization of Europe's telecoms
markets on January 1 next year.
</P>
<P>
Peter Bonfield, BT chief executive, said on Tuesday: "We must
be present in this market to fulfill our ambitions to be the number
one pan-European operator." 
</P>
