<HEADLINE> UK Royal Yacht Britannia to Be Permanently Preserved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 10 (Xinhua) -- British Defense Secretary
George Robertson announced here today that Britain's Royal Yacht
Britannia is to be permanently preserved as a corporate
hospitality center or a tourist attraction.
</P>
<P>
Speaking in a written answer to the parliament, Robertson said:
"I have decided that Britannia should be preserved for the wider
public benefit."
</P>
<P>
After Britannia's final voyage to Hong Kong for the handover
ceremony in June, it is widely debated that the Royal Yacht would
either be scrapped or preserved as a heritage legacy.
</P>
<P>
Robertson noted that it would be wrong to scrap the Royal
vessel, which "has a special place in the people's affections".
</P>
<P>
The Defense Secretary said that the Ministry of Defense had
considered several imaginative ideas for its future and had now
narrowed the choice down to two.
</P>
<P>
Under the new proposal, Britannia could either be used for a
corporate hospitality center on Edinburgh's Firth of Forth
waterfront or become the centerpiece of heritage site near
Manchester. 
</P>
</TEXT>
