<HEADLINE> 2 Drug Traffickers Seized in Zanzibar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Police have arrested
two Zanzibar residents and impounded 1.5 kilograms of heroin
(worth about 24,000 US dollars) imported from Bombay of India, an
official in charge of the Anti-Drug Unit told reporters today.
</P>
<P>
Esaka Mugasa said here that the two suspects were nabbed by
the Anti-Narcotics Unit (ANU) at Zanzibar International Airport
on Tuesday, with the contraband sealed in lady's slippers which
were carried as gifts for relatives.
</P>
<P>
He said the alleged traffickers were caught as they were
disembarking from Gulf Air No. GF 711/09. The first one,
Abdulrahmani Sheikh Rajabu, 34, was seized with one kilogram of
heroin sealed in five lady's slippers.
</P>
<P>
Mugasa named the second alleged suspect as Hamisi Abubakar
Machano, 27, who was nabbed with 500 grams of heroin sealed in
two lady's slippers.
</P>
<P>
The suspects were from Bombay via Muscat to the Zanzibar
isles, Mugasa noted.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, the two will appear before the
court soon.
</P>
<P>
Last May, a Dar es Salaam resident, Salum Mbwana, 25, was
booked at the same airport. He was found to have swallowed 250
grams of the same drug worth 2.5 million Shillings (about 4,000
US Dollars). Mbwana was nabbed as he was disembarking from Gulf
Air from Bombay through Muscat.
</P>
<P>
The Anti-drug Unit chief has given warnings to drug
traffickers that it is in vain to adopt the mushrooming practice
of sealing the drugs in lady's slippers and other newly
formulated methods. 
</P>
</TEXT>
