<HEADLINE> Arafat Urges Islamic Help to Save Jerusalem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian National Authority
President Yasser Arafat today appealed to Islamic leaders for
united efforts to save the Holy Qods (Jerusalem) from being
judaized.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the Islamic summit today, Arafat, who looked tired,
urged Muslims around the world to "rise to the level of the great
responsibility" when the Mideast peace process is facing acute
crisis.
</P>
<P>
Arafat arrived here Monday to attend the eighth summit of the
Organization of Islamic Conference, which lasts from Tuesday to
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"I hope that we could overcome our differences and unite our
work faithfully to save the Holy Qods" from plots to "eliminate
its Arab and Islamic identity and jeopardize its civilization,
historical and heritage features and noble spiritual and religious
status," Arafat said.
</P>
<P>
He was referring to Israel's construction of Jewish settlements
in the traditionally Arab East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The peace talks between the Palestinians and Israel have been
deadlocked due to Israel's retreat from the peace agreements
signed with the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
Arafat said that Israel has decided to build more settlements
in an attempt to isolate Jerusalem from its Palestinian
surroundings.
</P>
<P>
It also plans to construct the "temple of Solomon, to replace
Al Aqsa Mosque after its demolishing," he warned.
</P>
<P>
He urged Islamic leaders to "act quickly and sincerely to
rescue it and to defeat that Israeli plan" and show solidarity
with the city of Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
"Peace can not be realized unless the occupied Holy Qods
returns to its legitimate owners as the capital of the
independent Palestinian State," he emphasized. 
</P>
</TEXT>
