<HEADLINE> OAU Chief Praises UNHCR Efforts in Assisting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 10 (Xinhua) -- OAU secretary general
Salim Ahmed Salim today spoke highly of the efforts made by
United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) in
assisting African refugees.
</P>
<P>
Salim expressed his appreciation during his meeting with
Sergio de Mello, U.N. assistant high commissioner for refugees,
who is currently visiting Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
According to a press release of the Organization of African
Unity (OAU), Salim and de Mello exchanged views on humanitarian
issues in the Great Lakes region and on the flood situation in
Somalia.
</P>
<P>
The OAU chief also expressed satisfaction over the cooperation
between the pan-African grouping and the UNHCR which has
facilitated action on addressing the concerns of the governments
in the region and the refugees themselves.
</P>
<P>
The two stressed in particular the need to avoid the
increasing tendency toward compassion fatigue which has eroded
much of the well known African condition of caring for refugees,
the press release said.
</P>
<P>
As a reflection of OAU's concern over the recent flood
disaster in Somalia, Salim handed de Mello a check for 50,000
U.S. Dollars on behalf of the OAU as a token gesture to assist
those affected by floods in Somalia.
</P>
<P>
De Mello promised that the donation would be used for an
emergency package consisting of items such as medicine, food and
tents for the refugees and that the UNHCR would continue to work
in collaboration with the OAU and others in extending
humanitarian assistance to those in need, the press release
added. 
</P>
