<HEADLINE> Russia, Georgia to Normalize Border Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 10 (Xinhua) -- After border post dispute with
Georgia, Russian border guards have resumed the examination of
vehicles leaving Georgia, a high ranking officer told reporters on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The commander of Russia's special Caucasian border guard
district, Lieutenant-General Yevgeny Bolkhovitin said "our border
guards acted tactfully and calmly" when a group of Georgian young
people tried to picket a Russian border guard post.
</P>
<P>
He said "the distance between border guards and picketers did
not close to less than three meters... Common sense prevailed".
</P>
<P>
At the same time Bolkhovitin stressed that "we have the right
to post border guards where we believe it necessary in order to
ensure the security of the state border.
</P>
<P>
Both Russia and Georgia have agreed to resume the work of
commissions in charge of delimiting the countries' common border.
</P>
<P>
The Georgian Foreign Ministry made a statement last Friday
saying that Georgia will discontinue working with the commissions
to protest the moving of a Russian border post in the vicinity of
the village Verkhny lars deeper towards Georgian territory, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
During the visit of Deputy Prime Minister Valery Serov to
Tbilisi on December 8-9, the two countries agreed that the post
would be returned to its former position in the Daryal Canyon in
Russia's North Ossetia.
</P>
<P>
The two sides have also signed a protocol establishing the
return of border posts to the positions they occupied in July
1997. 
</P>
