<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-10 21:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israeli Anti-PNA Census Bill Passes First </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Knesset (parliament)
Wednesday evening passed the first reading of a legislation bill
prohibiting the Palestinian National Authority (PNA) to conduct
census in disputed East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The first reading of the bill was passed with a vote of 35-22.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Wednesday afternoon, Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu
opened the debate of the bill by declaring Jerusalem as the sole
and unified capital of Israel and it will remain so forever.
</P>
<P>
This legislation bill will prohibit all "illegal activities"
of the Palestinians in East Jerusalem and it is a test of
difficult struggle of Israel ahead, said Netanyahu.
</P>
<P>
"It is not only the test of the government, but the test of the
Israeli people," he added.
</P>
<P>
Netanyahu called on the opposition to support the bill.
</P>
<P>
Although they voted in favor of the legislation, the Labor
Party MPs criticized the government for formulating such a bill at
this time, which they said will create more conflicts with the PNA.
</P>
<P>
The timing of submitting and passing of this bill is terrible,
Labor Party chairman Ehud Barak told the Knesset.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Shimon Peres, another Labor Party MP and former
prime minister, called on the government to accept the proposal of
asking some independent organizations to conduct census for the
PNA in East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
MPs from the opposition Meretz Party voted against the
legislation bill, saying the rest of the world may consider the
legislation as another step of making obstacles for the second
phase of Israeli troop redeployment in the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
A ministerial committee approved the amendments of this bill
Tuesday night, which prohibits all kinds of activities of the PNA
in East Jerusalem and gives the public security minister the legal
authority to prevent the PNA from conducting census there.
</P>
<P>
According to Justice Minister Tzahi Hanegbi, violators of this
legislation will be sentenced to at least three years in jail.
</P>
<P>
As the Israeli Knesset struggling to pass this legislation
bill, PNA's census in Gaza Strip and the West Bank went on very
smoothly throughout the day today.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of census staff conducted door-to-door census, while
collecting copies of census questionnaires filled by the
Palestinian families.
</P>
<P>
The census is scheduled to be completed on December 24 and
final results will be announced on January 4, 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
