<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Rice Exports Up, but Earnings Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 11 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's rice exports were up
17 percent in the past 11 months but earnings were reportedly down
compared with the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The exports, of nearly 3.3 million metric tons, were close to
the Vietnamese government's projection of 3.6 million tons for the
entire year, or 600,000 tons more than last year.
</P>
<P>
But earnings from the exports were 50 million U.S. dollars
less, due to a drop of rice prices at the world market, said
official Vietnamese media reports available on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Mismanagement of rice purchase and exports were also to be
blamed for the decrease.
</P>
<P>
The government said this year's total grain output could be
equivalent to 30.6 million tons of paddy rice, including more than
9 million tons of commercial paddy rice.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development plans to
continue to designate and build infrastructure for export rice
growing areas, streamline export procedures, so as to increase the
number of direct exporters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
