<HEADLINE> Central Economic Conference Held in Beijing (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 11 (Xinhua) -- The Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) and the State Council held their
annual Central Economic Conference in Beijing between December
9-11.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin, who is also general secretary of
the central committee of CPC, presented an important address
concerning the current international and domestic situation,
implementation of various economic tasks designated by the 15th
CPC National Congress, and the key points and focus of the Chinese
economy in the coming year.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, premier and member of the Standing Committee of the
Political Bureau of CPC Central Committee; Zhu Rongji,
vice-premier and member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of CPC Central Committee; also presented speeches reviewing
and previewing the country's economic work.
</P>
<P>
Other Party and state leaders attending the three-day meeting
included Qiao Shi, Liu Huaqing, Hu Jintao, Wei Jianxing and Li
Lanqing.
</P>
<P>
According to the conference, the leadership of the CPC Central
Committee with Jiang Zemin as the core and the guidance of Deng
Xiaoping Theory and the basic line of the Party have enabled China
to score notable achievements in reform, opening and the socialist
moderization drive. China's economy has registered sustained and
sound development, with the basic realization of all economic
targets set within the framework of macroeconomic adjustments.
</P>
<P>
China's agriculture sector has once again recorded good harvest
this year despite the adverse effect of severe natural
disasters. The rural economy has experienced comprehensive
development.
</P>
<P>
The industrial sector has witnessed the deepening of enterprise
reform, with steady growth in industrial production and relatively
better economic returns.
</P>
<P>
The fact that financial revenues have increased by a wide
margin has helped to ensure financial stability.
</P>
<P>
Income levels have kept growing along with constant
improvements in living standards.
</P>
</TEXT>
