<DOCNO> XIE19971211.0071 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Central Economic Conference Held in Beijing (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The conference emphasized that China will continue to adopt the
principle of "recording progress while maintaining stability" in
economic operations.
</P>
<P>
According to the conference, "maintaining stability" means that
China will continue to adopt the moderately tight monetary policy,
curb inflation, stabilize and enhance the status of agriculture,
prevent and resolve financial risks, improve the social security
system and maintain a stable macroeconomic and social environment.
</P>
<P>
"Making progress" refers to the fact that China should register
new breakthroughs in state enterprise reform, financial system
reform and various other reform efforts. In addition, new measures
will be introduced to resolve important social
issues. Advancements should also be made in economic structural
readjustments and opening in order to markedly improve China's
overall economic strength and efficiency.
</P>
<P>
The conference noted that stability is the basis for advancing
forward the reform and development, and progress is China's
target.
</P>
