<HEADLINE> Central Economic Conference Held in Beijing (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The conference, which outlined a number of major tasks for
China's economic sector in 1998, stressed that the status of
agriculture as the economic base should be further reinforced in
order to achieve overall agricultural development.
</P>
<P>
Based on the current good situation and successive good
harvests, a clear mind should be maintained and investments in the
agricultural sector should be steadily increased, according to the
conference.
</P>
<P>
The fact that the country is implementing a national
development strategy and is attaching great significance to
economic development dictates that greater priority should be
placed on the agricultural sector.
</P>
<P>
The conference called for the optimization of the rural
economic structure, improvement in agricultural infrastructure and
the ecological environment, and further strengthening the status
of agriculture as the economic base in order to ensure the growth
of the agricultural production, increase the income level of
farmers and ensure stability in the countryside.
</P>
<P>
The Party's basic work policies in rural areas should remain
stable, especially in terms of the policy of land contractual
system, the policy to further reduce economic burdens on farmers
and the policy governing grain and cotton purchases and sales, in
order to protect the initiative of farmers.
</P>
<P>
The conference called for accelerating reform of the country's
grain and cotton purchase systems in an active and appropriate way
in order to establish a new marketing system and pricing mechanism.
</P>
<P>
The conference also called for the accelerated construction of
agricultural infrastructure, including water conservancy,
agricultural science and technology, cultivatable land and the
ecological environment in order to enhance the integrated capacity
of agricultural production.
</P>
<P>
While optimizing the economic structure in rural areas and
maintaining the steady growth of grain, the nation should also
extend great efforts to develop the plantation, cultivation and
processing industries in the countryside, the conference stressed.
</P>
<P>
China should continue along the track of industrializing the
agricultural sector and increase both the value and efficiency of
the sector, according to the conference.
</P>
</TEXT>
