<HEADLINE> Central Economic Conference Held in Beijing (5) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The conference pledged to complete the crucial stage in
restructuring of the state-owned enterprises in order to improve
the managerial status of state firms.
</P>
<P>
The conference noted that the reform of state enterprises is
regarded as the key to the nation's overall economic restructuring
drive, and stressed that the pressing task of current economic
work is to restructure and develop state firms.
</P>
<P>
The 15th Party Congress's targets for restructuring state-owned
enterprises included: enabling the majority loss-making medium- to
large-sized state-owned enterprises escape current difficulties
within three years, while enabling the majority of the large and
medium-sized state-owned back-bone enterprises to initially adopt
a modern enterprise system by restructuring, regrouping, carrying
out renovations and reinforcing management.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, the textile industry is expected to record major
breakthroughs in efforts to establish a modern enterprise system
for companies to substantially improve the management of various
state enterprises, according to the conference.
</P>
<P>
The conference called for active efforts to strategically
regroup state firm by attaching greater attention to larger firms
and relaxing controls on smaller enterprises.
</P>
<P>
A number of large enterprise groups will be established in
various key industries or related sectors through introducing
regrouping, mergers, leasing and contracting, according to the
conference.
</P>
<P>
Policies encouraging mergers, bankruptcies, reducing excessive
redundancies and reemployment programs will be continued in order
to realize mechanisms for competition and reasonable flow of
labor. The conference also pointed out that enterprises should
strengthen their sense of competition and risk.
</P>
<P>
The conference also pledged to reinforce Party leaderships of
enterprises, urging them to serve as the core and persist in the
principle of relying on the working class. It also called for
restructuring the government to realize the separation of
government and enterprises, introduce efficient supervision and
operational mechanisms for the state properties; and accelerate
and improve the social security system.
</P>
</TEXT>
