<HEADLINE> 18 People Killed in Car Crash in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 11 (Xinhua) -- A collision between a
minibus and a truck on Wednesday night claimed 18 lives near
Melmoth, northern Kwazulu-Natal in South Africa, the South
African Press Association reported today.
</P>
<P>
Melmoth is about 100 kilometers north of Durban.
</P>
<P>
A Kwazulu-Natal traffic information officer said today that
the minibus carrying 18 people collided with the truck after the
driver of the minibus tried to overtake a vehicle on the
Ulundi-Melmoth road in rain and mist at about 9 p.m. (1900 GMT).
</P>
<P>
The truck driver and two others were critically injured.
</P>
<P>
Traffic accidents usually peak at the Christmas season in
South Africa. A spokesman of the Kwazulu-Natal Department of
Transport said the accident was a severe blow to a traffic
holiday project launched in Durban on Tuesday. 
</P>
