<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh May Face Severe Earthquakes in Future: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 11 (Xinhua) -- Scientists and engineers have
warned that Bangladesh may face severe earthquakes in future and
urged the government to take steps to identify vulnerable areas,
localities and structures as precautions against the possible
disaster, a local newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
They observed with concern that despite the apprehension of
tremor strikes, little preparedness have been adopted to contain
the disaster, The New Nation said.
</P>
<P>
The opinions and suggestions came at a seminar organized by a
disaster preparedness network recently in Dhaka.
</P>
<P>
The recommendations of the seminar included the establishment
of a national committee, disaster management agencies and
lifelines such as water supply, fire services and others,
extensive study of earthquake activities by establishing a
national level research institute, and development of a national
contingency plan for earthquake disaster mitigation.
</P>
<P>
Installing an extensive seismological observatory network with
a central unit at Dhaka is also included in the recommendations.
</P>
</TEXT>
