<HEADLINE> Glimsdal Takes Surprise Biathlon Win </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, December 11 (Xinhua) -- Norwegian Sylfest Glimsdal
made his first World Cup podium appearance in three years with a
surprise win in a men's 20-km biathlon in Ostersund, Sweden, on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Glimsdal topped a field of 116 competitors from 31 nations and
regions, covering an icy course in 49 minutes, 19.0 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Russians took the next two spots with Alexei Kobelev finishing
08.7 seconds behind and Viktor Malgourev 21.3 seconds off the pace.
</P>
<P>
World Cup leader Dag Bjorndalen of Norway was fifth behind
Italian Patrick Favre.  
