<HEADLINE> Elections of Labor Conciliation Boards Held in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 11 (Xinhua) -- The elections of labor
conciliation boards in industrial enterprises were held on
Wednesday across France.
</P>
<P>
The elections, the first since 1992, attracted only one third
of the 14.6 million workers concerned with conciliation boards,
Agence France-Presse (AFP) reported.
</P>
<P>
The national union of Confederation Generale du Travail (CGT)
remained on top of the list with 33.1 percent of the votes,
followed by the Confederation Francaise Democratique du Travail
and the Force Ouvriere, with 25.3 and 20.5 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
The Coordination Francaise Nationale des Travailleurs, a union
close to the extreme-right National Front, participated in the
elections for the first time and won 2.2 percent of the votes with
its members elected in Paris and Marseille regions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
