<DOCNO> XIE19971211.0104 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roundup: OAU Makes Progress in Mediating Comorian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
(by Chen Cailin)
</P>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 11 (Xinhua) -- Mediation efforts of the
Organization of African Unity (OAU) has finally succeeded in
gathering all the concerned parties to the Comoros crisis to sit
at the table for a peaceful solution to the crisis.
</P>
<P>
A four-day international conference on Comoros, organized by
the OAU and now going on in the capital of Ethiopia, is attended
by delegations representing the federal government, different
political forces and the islands of Anjouan, Moheli and Grand
Comoros.
</P>
<P>
This is the progress the OAU has achieved after over four
months mediation of the crisis.
</P>
<P>
On August 3 this year, separatists from the Anjouan Island,
one of four islands of the Comoros, announced their independence.
</P>
<P>
They set up so-called "the state of Anjouan", elected
"president" and announced to join France, the former colonial
ruler of the islands.
</P>
<P>
The separative activity was immediately opposed by the OAU
which maintains the sovereign and territorial integrity of member
states. OAU Secretary General Salim Ahmed Salim also appointed a
special envoy to Comoros for the mediation mission.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the OAU deployed military observers in the Island
of Moheli and Island of Grand Comoros. Because of the refuse of
the Anjouanese, the military observers have not been deployed at
the Island of Anjouan.
</P>
<P>
The clear-cut OAU stand and mediation efforts have received
support from the United Nations and the international community.
</P>
<P>
Now, all the Comorian delegations attending the conference
have agreed to seek a peaceful and negotiated settlement of the
crisis.
</P>
<P>
According to the OAU, the current consultations between the
Comorian delegations will be based on two fundamental factors,
which are "the legitimate concerns and interests of all the
islands" and "the need to preserve the unity and territorial
integrity of the country."
</P>
<P>
The current Comorian crisis, in the final analysis, is a
crisis of socio-economic and its root cause is poverty and
underdevelopment.
</P>
<P>
Salim pointed out "unless the issue of poverty and
underdevelopment is seriously addressed, the islands will
continue to be faced with instability."
</P>
<P>
Cognizant of this reality, the OAU working in tandem with the
League of Arab States, the European Union, the United Nations and
others is determined to mobilize international support and
assistance for socio-economic development of the Comoros.
</P>
<P>
The OAU efforts to help the eradication of factors of
instability of the islands country will certainly receive the
appreciation and support of the Comorian people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971211.0105 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-11 13:41 </DATE_TIME>
