<HEADLINE> Mubarak Meets Former Israeli PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, December 11 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak
today held talks with former Israeli prime minister Shimon Peres
and his accompanying delegation at his residence.
</P>
<P>
Presidential Political Adviser Osama el-Baz attended the
meeting, which dealt with the latest developments of the stalled
Mideast peace process, mainly the Palestinian-Israeli track.
</P>
<P>
Peres arrived here this morning on a lightning visit to Egypt
amid a yawning gulf dividing Israel's right and left on the peace
process.
</P>
<P>
Peres, 74, held the prime minister's post from 1984 to 1986,
and again for seven months after his predecessor Yitzhak Rabin was
assassinated by a Jewish ultranationalist opposed to the
peacemaking two years ago. He lost 1996 general elections to
Benjamin Netanyahu. 
</P>
