<HEADLINE> Chinese, Uzbekistan Foreign Ministers Confer in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 11 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign
Minister Qian Qichen today conferred with visiting Uzbekistan
Foreign Minister Kamilov Abdulaziz Hafizovich.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that bilateral relations have developed steadily
since the establishment of diplomatic relations six years ago.
</P>
<P>
The leaders of the two countries have maintained contacts and
deepened mutual understanding and trust, he said, and the two
countries have engaged in bilateral political, economic, trade,
scientific, technological and cultural cooperation of mutual
benefit.
</P>
<P>
Qian told Hafizovich that the two countries share no any
conflicts of interests. The development of friendship and
cooperation between the two sides is an important component of
the good-neighborly diplomacy of China, he added.
</P>
<P>
Qian went on to say that China respects Uzbekistan's internal
and external policies and its sovereignty as well as
the road of development the Uzbekistan people have chosen.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral economic and trade cooperation constitutes an
important part of relations between the two countries, he
said. Bilateral trade volume is not big enough, but it is
increasing year by year.
</P>
<P>
He said the development of relations between the two countries
has great potentials and broad prospects. He said that although
they are not contiguous, they are neighbors.
</P>
<P>
The growth of the stable and friendly relations between the two
countries is in line with the fundamental interests and common
aspiration of the two countries and their peoples, he said.
</P>
<P>
Hafizovich said the two countries have done a lot to deepen
mutual understanding and enhance political, economic and trade
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said that China is a major country who plays an important
role in regional and global affairs. There exist no hurdles in
advancing bilateral relations, while enormous potentials exist for
bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Qian and Hafizovich also exchanged views on regional and
international issues of common concern and reached consensus.
</P>
<P>
After the talks, the two foreign ministers signed a treaty on
bilateral civilian and criminal judicial assistance and an
agreement on environmental protection.  
</P>
</TEXT>
