<HEADLINE> Connors Enters Semis of Champions Torney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, December 11 (Xinhua) -- Eight-time grand slam singles
champion Jimmy Connors fought back from one set down to win his
opening match at the inaugural Sydney stop of the Champions Tennis
tournament on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Connors, 45, winner of 130 ATP singles titles, beat Australia's
John Fitzgerald 4-6, 6-1, 10-5 to enter the semifinals.
</P>
<P>
Under the Champions format, matches are played as best of three
sets but the third set is played as a tiebreak, with the winner
being the first to win 10 points.
</P>
<P>
Connors will next take on compatriot Tim Wilkison, who earlier
defeated two-times Australian Open winner Guillermo Vilas of
Argentina.
</P>
<P>
The 45-year-old Vilas was no match for the American, going down
in straight sets 6-3, 6-2.  
</P>
