<HEADLINE> Cooperation between Airbus Industrie and China Increasing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 11 (Xinhua) -- China will take delivery of 19
Airbus planes in 1998, the European Airbus Industrie announced
here today.
</P>
<P>
Airbus vows to achieve a 50 percent share in China's airliner
market in a couple of years, it said.
</P>
<P>
Since the Shanghai-based China Eastern Airlines became the
first Chinese customer of Airbus Industrie in 1985, the large
aircraft manufacturer in the world has got confirmed orders for 92
airliners from China, including 60 A320-series airliners, and 47
of them have already gone into operation.
</P>
<P>
Airbus Industrie will deliver a total of 19 airplanes to China
for the whole year of 1997.
</P>
<P>
The CASC/Airbus Aviation Training Center, a joint effort of
Airbus and the China Aviation Supplies Import and Export
Corporation, held a ceremony today to mark the completion of
training for the first two pilots of the China Northwestern
Airlines.
</P>
<P>
The center, with an investment of 80 million US dollars from
Airbus Industrie, has also helped to train 850 attendants for
China's airlines, since it was set up several months ago.
</P>
<P>
Airbus Industrie has also participated in another key project
to develop 100-seat airliners together with the China Aviation
Industrial Corporation and a technology company of Singapore.
</P>
<P>
Airbus Industrial predicts that China needs 1,320 airliners
from now to 2014, with a combined value of 100 billion US
dollars. It has to compete fiercely in the Chinese market with
another aircraft manufacturing giant, the new Boeing company,
which was merged by Boeing and McDonnell Douglas not long ago.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
