<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's First Partnership Fund With Foreign Investment Set Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 11 (Xinhua) -- China's first partnership fund
with foreign investments was formally set up here today.
</P>
<P>
The Partnership Fund set joinly by the Chinese and Swiss
governments has a fund of 31.25 million SFr., 20 percent of which
was contributed by the Chinese government, which is represented by
the State Development Bank of China (SDB), China's biggest policy
bank dedicated to the medium and long-term financing for the state
infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
The fund will provide financial support to both Chinese
companies and medium and small-sized Swiss companies in China in
the Chinese currency and foreign currencies.
</P>
<P>
The founding ceremony was held this evening at the Great Hall
of the People in Beijing. Chen Yuan, vice president of the People's
Bank of China, and officials from the Federal Office of Foreign
Economic Affairs of Switzerland as well as diplomats from the
Swiss Embassy in China attended the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
SDB has provided 27.7 million yuan of loans for China's key
capital construction projects and technical renovation projects
during its three-year history. Its feats also include pooling funds
through selling bonds in Japan and the US. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
