<HEADLINE> Women's Super-G Rained out </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 11 (Xinhua) -- The women's World Cup Super-G
slalom was forced to be cancelled by heavy fog and drizzle in the
French resort Val D'Isere on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Officials will meet later in the day to decide whether or not
the race should be run on Sunday just before the men's downhill.
</P>
<P>
Showers started early in the morning, sweeping fresh snow off
the top of the Oreiller Killy piste on which four races were
scheduled for the weekend.
</P>
<P>
Organisers said a women's giant slalom planned for Friday would
go ahead as planned.
</P>
<P>
The super-G could be moved to Saturday, the same day as a men's
downhill. Racing ends on Sunday with a men's giant slalom. 
