<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Customs Against Counterfeits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 11 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Customs seized a
large amount of counterfeit clothing and Chinese patent medicine
in a two-day operation here.
</P>
<P>
Officers of the Customs and Excise Department confiscated
250,000 bottles of Chinese patent medicine and 5,350 pieces of
counterfeit clothing bearing various forged famous Italian, French
and American trade marks. Four men were arrested.
</P>
<P>
The total value of the seizure was estimated to reach one
million HK dollars (128,000 US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Sources from the Customs said that apart from taking vigorous
enforcement actions against copyright privacy, the department also
pays equal attention to the fight against counterfeiters. 
