<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Film Actress Donates Awards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 11 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong actress Josephine
Siao today donated her 11 film awards to the local film archive,
which is speeding up a "collection campaign" in preserving the
film heritage.
</P>
<P>
Siao went on the silver screen at childhood, and won "Best
Child Actor Award" in 1955 at the second Southeast Asian Film
Festival for the film "Orphan Girl".
</P>
<P>
She was praised as an evergreen tree in the film circle,
picking up the "Best Actress Award" at the seventh Hong Kong Film
Awards for "Wrong Couples" in 1988, "Ten Best Actors of the World"
in 1996, and "Artist of the Year" in 1997. Two recent films in
which she played a role, "Summer Snow" and "Hu Du Men", also
gained local and international awards.
</P>
<P>
Ronald Leung, chairman of the Provisional Urban Council, said
at a souvenir presentation ceremony today that the awards
represented the high artistic achievement of Siao in her film
career.
</P>
<P>
The awards and selected materials from the "collection
campaign" will be displayed by the Hong Kong Film Archive during
the 22nd International Film Festival in April 1998.
</P>
<P>
The film archive is collecting film oldies, pictures, scripts,
contracts, catalogues, and press clippings.  
</P>
