<HEADLINE> China, US Launch Undersea Optical Cable Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 11 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese and US governments
today in Washington signed an agreement on construction and
maintenance of an undersea optical cable project linking the two
countries and a contract on the building of the project, an
official with Ministry of Post and Telecommunications (MPT) told
Xinhua here today.
</P>
<P>
The official said the two documents marked the start-up of the
Sino-US optical cable project, slated to be completed and
operational in 1999.
</P>
<P>
The proposal for the project was raised by China Telecom, the
country's largest telecom operator, and AT&AMP;T of the United
States. It has won active response and support from other
transnational telecom corporations.
</P>
<P>
The MPT official considered the project a milestone for the two
countries in telecom construction and a foundation for
Asia-Pacific region to build itself into one of the key telecom
hubs worldwide in the next century.
</P>
<P>
Wu Jichuan, Chinese minister of Post and Telecommunications,
representatives from 14 organs that initiated the project and 36
enterprises that will participate in the construction were present
at the signing ceremony, according to the official.
</P>
<P>
The rapid development of the global communications and roaring
businesses demand more capable telecom networks. To meet the ever
increasing requirements, China Telecom in recent years launched
joint optical cable projects with Japan and the Republic of
Korea. The corporation also joined the construction of Euroasia
inter-continental optical cable project. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
