<HEADLINE> China to Put More Emphasis on Technology for Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 11 (Xinhua) -- China will encourage research
centers to co-operate with business, according to Xu Guanhua,
vice-minister of the State Science and Technology Commission, who
said that China will place more emphasis on the role of science
and technology in economic growth, and use them to solve economic
development problems.
</P>
<P>
Xu said that China will give priority to 500 science and
technology service centers for the rest of this century to help
small and medium-sized enterprises.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the country will encourage technology development
centers in industries to aid large enterprises in solving key
technology problems.
</P>
<P>
China has had rapid economic growth since the early 1980s, but
quality and returns are not so satisfactory, experts said. Xu
points out that the main reason is a weakness in the development
of new technology.
</P>
<P>
Xu also said that China will make full use of technology in
transforming traditional industries and developing agriculture.
</P>
<P>
"Priority should be given to the promotion of intellectual
power in industries, and the employment of biological and
information technology in reforming traditional agriculture," he
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
