<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Floods Cut off Uganda's Roads </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 11 (Xinhua) -- President Yoweri Museveni's
motorcade stranded on Kampala-Gulu highway for some 30 minutes
near Wabulenzi, some 30 kilometers north of Kampala.
</P>
<P>
Locals hewed wood and collected stones to fill the hole into
which a car of the six-vehicle motorcade was falling. The
president was not on the motorcade.
</P>
<P>
Torrential rains in three recent months had cut off transport
in some areas in Uganda, The New Vision reported today.
</P>
<P>
In the south-western Kabale District, road linking Rwanda and
Uganda through Katuna was blocked by landslides from Katuna to
Kabale Town.
</P>
<P>
Parts of the road near the border was completely damaged, and
heavy trucks were advised to go other ways, reports from the
scene said.
</P>
<P>
Heavy rains also damaged Rubaya sub-county in the district and
parts of Rubaale in the neighbour district of Ntungamo.
</P>
<P>
In western district of Bushenyi, the roads in Igara become
impassable, and in another western district of Mbarara, the roads
between the town of Mbarara and Ibanda is disrupted and the
collection of milk was forced to be stopped.
</P>
<P>
In the central district of Masaka, only high vehicles and
pedestrians could cross the flooded roads.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports said floods devastated transport in western
district of Kasese, Bundibugyo and eastern district of Mbale,
Iganga, Pallisa and Kapchorwa districts.
</P>
<P>
Uganda has 45 districts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
