<HEADLINE> Hong Kong's Chief Executive Talks With Press In Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 11 (Xinhua) -- At a press conference here
today, Tung Chee-hwa, Chief Executive of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR), said that he was "greatly encouraged"
by the central government's understanding and support when he came
here to give his first progress report.
</P>
<P>
Tung said that central government leaders think highly of the
SAR government's work after July 1, and his progress report
increased understanding and exchanges between Hong Kong and inland
areas, and he himself has gotten a better look at current economic
development of inland areas.
</P>
<P>
He said that Hong Kong has maintained close economic ties
with inland areas in the past and their prosperity has helped Hong
Kong's development.
</P>
<P>
Tung said he is satisfied with the SAR government's work since
its establishment five months ago and that everything has gone
smoothly since Hong Kong's return to the motherland. Because of
appropriate government measures, the economy is growing and people
are confident about Hong Kong's political and economic futures, he
said.
</P>
<P>
He also pointed out that civil servants in Hong Kong have had
more exchanges with inland counterparts and that the SAR will
increase those exchanges.
</P>
<P>
He said that recent financial crisis in Southeast Asia had not
had much influence in Hong Kong, thanks to its solid economic
foundation, proper SAR government policies, and central government
support and assistance.
</P>
<P>
The crisis did cause Hong Kong to make some readjustments of
its stock market and real estate market, but, that these
readjustments were "healthy", he emphasized.
</P>
<P>
Tung said the SAR will increase economic and cultural exchanges
with Taiwan to play a positive role in the reunification of the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
He added that the SAR government is preparing to set up
an office in Beijing and the central government has promised to
support the plan. 
</P>
