<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Life Expectancy Increases in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 11 (Xinhua) -- The average life expectancy of
Macao residents has increased by 9.84 years over the past two
decades, the latest statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics Department
show that average life expectancy between 1969 and 1972 reached
66.73 years, but it grew to 76.57 years during the 1993-1996
period.
</P>
<P>
As usual, women tend to live longer than men. They survive
their male counterparts by between 4.87 and 8.31 years in the
1969-1996 period.
</P>
<P>
The calculation was made on a four-year basis, involving the
overall population, their age and sex and the mortality rate of
different age groups.
</P>
<P>
In addition, life expectancy in Macao has become one of the
highest in the region.
</P>
<P>
While Macao residents live one or two years less than those in
Hong Kong, they outlive the Japanese by two to three years. They
also live seven to eight years longer than residents in China's
inland areas.
</P>
<P>
The number of Macao residents reached 420,300 by the end of
September this year. About 97 percent are Chinese nationals and
the remaining Portuguese and other foreign nationals.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
