<HEADLINE> Farmers' Incomes In Northwest China Increasing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, December 11 (Xinhua) -- Per capita incomes of rural
people in northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region are
expected to reach 1,580 yuan this year, and increase of six
percent when adjusted for inflation.
</P>
<P>
In Ningxia's poverty-stricken Xihaigu region, 200,000 have
escaped poverty and have adequate food and clothing this year.
</P>
<P>
The autonomous region has undergone rural economic reforms and
is building open-market forestry, animal husbandry, fishery, and
other production bases focused on processing agricultural products
and increasing the use of technology.
</P>
<P>
This year, the autonomous region produced 2.57 million tons of
grain, a record high, and had marked increases in beet, aquatic
products, and meat output.
</P>
<P>
Animal husbandry has become a major source of income increases
of the farmers, and the development of rural and township
enterprises, and the service trade has been another means. In the
first nine months of this year, rural and township enterprises had
6.49 billion yuan of output value, up 26.5 percent from the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
Per capita income of farmers for working in industry and the
service trade will amount to 316 yuan, accounting for 20 percent
of their total income. 
</P>
</TEXT>
