<HEADLINE> Indonesia to Launch Telecommunications Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 11 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian government will
officially launch Telematika Indonesia, an ambitious
telecommunications project to prepare the country for entry into
the information technology era, an official said here today.
</P>
<P>
The project consists of an integrated program to develop the
country's telecommunications infrastructure, its application and
human resources, Director General of Post and Telecommunications
Djakaria Purawidjaja said.
</P>
<P>
He said Telematika Indonesia is based on the Nusantara 21
information superhighway project developed by the Ministry of
Tourism, Post and Telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
"Nusantara 21 is a concept and vision for the country's
telecommunications sector in the 21st century," he said.
</P>
<P>
"On January 15, Telematika will be revealed, just wait and see.
We have prepared a very thick manuscript," he said. But he refused
to give further details.
</P>
<P>
Nusantara 21 is Indonesia's mega-telecommunications plan for
entering the information technology era. The project is designed
to connect the whole archipelago to the information superhighway
through multimedia networks, sources at the Tourism, Post and
Telecommunications Ministry said earlier.
</P>
<P>
The project, which will involve both private and government
participation, is defined as an integration of telecommunications
and computing hardware and software having the main components of
telecommunications, the computer industry and television
broadcasting, as well as the media industry, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
To enhance the project, a team comprising 14 cabinet ministers
has been formed to help usher Indonesia into the information
superhighway era.  
</P>
</TEXT>
