<HEADLINE> Ramos Names New Chief of Staff of Armed Forces </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 11 (Xinhua) -- President Fidel Ramos today
named army chief Clemente Mariano as the new chief of staff of the
Armed Forces of the Philippines effective January 1.
</P>
<P>
Mariano will replace Arnulfo Acedera who will retire on
December 31 after reaching the mandatory retirement age of 65.
</P>
<P>
Acedera is due to retire on his birthday on December 19, but
the president extended his tour of duty for 12 days on the
recommendation of Defense Secretary Fortunato Abat for Acedera to
preside over the 61st anniversary of the armed forces on December
21.
</P>
<P>
Mariano, a graduate of the Philippine Military Academy, said he
would give top priority to the modernization of the armed forces
and the operations against insurgency and kidnapping after
assuming office. 
</P>
