<HEADLINE> Explosion Kills Two in Eastern Sri Lankan City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 11 (Xinhua) -- Two people were killed in an
explosion in the Eastern city of Batticaloa this morning, Military
Spokesman Ink Dewage said here today.
</P>
<P>
The explosion took place inside a three wheeler vehicle at
around 10:30. A passenger and the owner of the vehicle were killed
as a result of the explosion.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman didn't give further details. He said police
investigations were underway.
</P>
<P>
This is the second explosion to hit the city in three days. On
Tuesday, a grenade thrown by a Tamil rebel exploded in a market,
killing three people and injuring 23 others.
</P>
<P>
Batticaloa is the second largest city in Eastern province where
rebels of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam are active.
</P>
</TEXT>
