<HEADLINE> Talks Between Kuwaiti Emir, Iranian Leaders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, December 11 (Xinhua) -- A Kuwaiti newspaper today
described the talks between the Kuwaiti emir and Iranian leaders
in Tehran on the sidelines of the summit of the Organization of
the Islamic Conference (OIC) as "highly fruitful."
</P>
<P>
A front page article carried by the English daily Arab Times
today quoted informed sources accompanying Kuwaiti Emir Sheikh
Jaber Al-Ahmed Al-Sabah to the three-day summit as saying that the
outcome of the talks "heralds a new chapter in the Kuwaiti-Iranian
ties on the one hand, and the Gulf-Iranian relations on the other."
</P>
<P>
The talks between the emir and Iranian supreme leader Ali
Khamenei and Iranian President Mohammad Khatami were very frank
and open, the article said.
</P>
<P>
The talks which centered on strengthening regional stability
and security would have a great impact on improving ties between
Kuwait and Iran, the sources were quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The sources disclosed that the two Iranian leaders showed
appreciation and understanding of the points raised by the
Kuwaiti emir, which reflected Kuwaiti and Gulf concerns.
</P>
<P>
The emir expressed great optimism at the future of relations
between the two countries and also between Iran and other Gulf
Arab states.
</P>
<P>
The past year has seen signs of improvement of relations
between Iran and the Gulf Cooperation Council states. Iran has
taken various initiatives to warm up its ties with the Gulf Arab
states, namely, Saudi Arabia, the United Arab Emirates, Oman,
Qatar, Bahrain as well as Kuwait. All these countries have
responded positively.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait and Iran, which have been on relatively good terms,
exchanged many official visits and further expanded their
bilateral trade volumes.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that during the talks, the Kuwaiti emir
emphasized the need to deal with differences and disputes
through dialogue and negotiations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
