<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Hears Progress Report from Hong Kong Chief Executive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 11 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
today listened to the first progress report by Tung Chee-hwa,
Chief Executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(SAR). Tung assumed office on July 1.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said the Hong Kong SAR has maintained social and
political stability since its establishment. Although the
financial turmoil of Southeast Asia has had some impact on Hong
Kong, Hong Kong still remains economically healthy, he said.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong people continue to retain their original lifestyle
and enjoy a wide range of democracy and freedom, Jiang noted. All
these demonstrate that the SAR is operating smoothly under the
framework of "Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong" with a high
degree of autonomy, prescribed in the Basic Law, he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Hong Kong residents have a deeper understanding on
the "one country, two systems" policy and the central government's
determination to carrying out the policy, he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that in the past five months the Hong Kong SAR
government led by Tung has made remarkable achievements through
hard work.
</P>
<P>
Facts show that Hong Kong people can administer their own
affairs and the SAR has a good beginning, he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang pledged that the central government will support Tung's
work, as well as the SAR in implementing the policies of "Hong
Kong people governing Hong Kong" and a high-degree of autonomy in
accordance with the Basic Law. The central government will never
interfere in affairs belonging to the SAR's autonomy, he added.
</P>
<P>
He also said he believes that with the strong backing of the
motherland, Hong Kong will have a better future.
</P>
<P>
Present on the occasion were Zeng Qinghong, director of the
General Office of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of
China, and Liao Hui, director of the State Council's Hong Kong and
Macao Affairs Office.  
</P>
</TEXT>
