<HEADLINE> China's Civil Aviation Industry Gets New Computer Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 11 (Xinhua) -- Thanks to an agreement between
the Civil Aviation Administration of China's Computer Center and
the US's Unisys Corp., signed on Tuesday, China's civil aviation
industry will soon be using a large CMOS computer that can handle
200 million customers annually.
</P>
<P>
The computer, valued at 15 million US dollars, is expected to
greatly improve the present computer network, and make it possible
to handle a larger number of air travelers in China over the next
few years.
</P>
<P>
The number of passengers has grown at a rate of roughly 20
percent annually for the past few years, and the figure reached
more than 55 million in 1996. This is expected to continue in
coming years, and the present network can not handle such a large
market.
</P>
<P>
The new computer was first put on the market earlier this
year. It is expected to arrive here late this month and will
go into trial operation next May. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
