<HEADLINE> Graf To Take on Hingis At Toray Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, December 11 (Xinhua) -- German veteran Steffi Graf will
exchange serves and volleys with Swiss sensation Martina Hingis
when she makes her comeback to the Toray Pan Pacific Open in
February in Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
The former world number one was forced to pull out of a
long-awaited final against Hingis after she aggravated a knee
tendon a year ago in Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
Graf consequentially missed the following three months to
recover, conceding her number one ranking to Hingis.
</P>
<P>
Graf returned to the German and French Opens before missing the
rest of the season to have an operation.
</P>
<P>
The 926,250 U.S. Dollars tournament, one of the biggest WTA
events outside the Grand Slam series, will also pitch Olympic
champion Lindsay Davenport of the United States, South African
Amanda Coetzer and French Open champion Iva Majoli of
