Premier Li Peng this year showed the importance China attaches to
the development of its friendly and cooperative relations with
African countries such as Cape Verde.
</P>
<P>
China and Cape Verde, both developing countries, have much in
common, he said. The Chinese government hopes to enhance
communications in various forms with African nations to make
further advances in friendship and cooperative links in all fields.
</P>
<P>
Rong thanked the Cape Verde government for its "one China"
position and its constant support to China on human rights issues.
</P>
<P>
He also briefed the visitors on China's economic development.
</P>
<P>
Fernandes said Cape Verde treasures the efforts made by the
Chinese government and its people to develop friendship and
cooperation with Cape Verde and other African countries.
</P>
<P>
Cape Verde hopes that western Africa would strengthen the links
with China, which is a great cooperative partner, in politics and
economy and other areas, he said.
</P>
<P>
Cape Verde and other African countries also value China's
experience in the field of economic development, and it would be
significant for African countries to make use of that experience,
he said.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed that China could continue to trust Cape
Verde's support on China's great cause of reunification and human
rights issues. 
</P>
</TEXT>
