<HEADLINE> More Efforts Urged to Eliminate Hunger in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 11 (Xinhua) -- More efforts are expected to
be made in Vietnam to eliminate hunger and alleviate poverty.
</P>
<P>
The Communist Party of Vietnam (CPV) has said recently that
greater efforts should be made to achieve the target set by last
year's CPV congress of reducing the country's rate of poor and
hungry households from 20-25 percent to 10 percent by the year
2000.
</P>
<P>
To reach the target requires a reduction of 300,000 poor
households a year.
</P>
<P>
The party also called for the gradual implementation of the
policy to cut all or part of school fees and grant scholarships
for children from poor households, and to cut all or part of
medical charges for poor people.
</P>
<P>
The campaign to eradicate hunger and reduce poverty has spread
nationwide and helped reduce the number of poor and hungry
households by two percent annually.
</P>
<P>
However, there are still nearly 2.9 million households, which
account for 19.3 percent of the country's total households.
</P>
</TEXT>
