<DOCNO> XIE19971211.0227 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Make Yangtze River Silting Model at Chongqing Port </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, December 11 (Xinhua) -- Early next year China will
make a model on silting of the section of the Yangtze River in
Chongqing Municipality early next year.
</P>
<P>
The model will provide a basis for discussions on harnessing
the Yangtze River in southwest China at Chongqing, a port on the
upper and middle reaches of the river.
</P>
<P>
Downstream of Chongqing, construction of the Three Gorges water
control project, the world's largest, is under construction. When
the project is completed in 2009, the upstream area of the dam will
be flooded and become a big reservoir, which is expected to cause
a major silting problem upstream, especially in the Chongqing Port
area.
</P>
<P>
The model will be used for feasibility research on silting law,
plans for comprehensively harnessing the port area of Chongqing
and navigation around the port city.
</P>
<P>
A normal design will be adopted in making the model which will
be built according to a scale of 1:50. The model will cover the
main port areas of Chongqing, including the section from Qiezi
River to Tongluo Gorge, and the section from Jialing River at
Chaotianmen to Jingkou.
</P>
<P>
The model will be 400 meters long, 7 meters wide and 2 meters
high. It will be placed in the Southwest China Water Transport
Engineering Science Institute of Chongqing Jiaotong College and it
is expected to be completed in August of 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
