<HEADLINE> Chinese Lifter Sets World Records in Women's 70kg Class </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHIANG MAI, Northern Thailand, December 11 (Xinhua) -- China's
women lifter Xiang Fenglan set three new world records in the
70-kilogram class at the world weightlifting championships here
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Xiang lifted 105.5 kilograms to set the new record in the
snatch and then rewrote the listed mark of clean and jerk with
130.5 kgs and also a new overall record with 235 kgs.
</P>
<P>
The previous world records were held by compatriots Yu Wenyu in
the snatch at 105 kgs, and 232.5 kgs overall, and Xu Lihua with
130 kgs in the jerk.
</P>
<P>
Chinese lifters have now set seven records at the current world
championships. 
