<HEADLINE> Indian Government Loosens Control of PSUs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 11 (Xinhua) -- The Indian government has
loosened its control over the public sector undertakings (PSUs) in
a bid to enhance the PSUs' operational efficiency.
</P>
<P>
The government has reduced the total number of guidelines for
PSUs from 892 to 196. While 696 guidelines have been canceled
with immediate effect, 25 are being modified and 171 are being
retained, official sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
Simultaneously, the Industry Ministry has appointed a committee
to examine the efficacy of the remaining 196 clauses. The new
committee is expected to submit its recommendations by March 1998.
</P>
