<HEADLINE> India to Have New Policy on Automobiles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 11 (Xinhua) -- All car companies in India
will have to sign fresh pacts with the government in accordance
with the new automobile policy, a government official said here
today.
</P>
<P>
Under the new policy, the minimum indigenization level is
expected to be reduced to 50 percent in three years as against 70
percent in five years announced earlier.
</P>
<P>
Also, a company failing to meet the indigenization level would
be penalized and its spare parts import licenses would not be
renewed.
</P>
<P>
The details of the new policy have been finalized by the
Director General of Foreign Trade and it is expected to be
announced by the Commerce Ministry before the end of this week.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the government had said that companies failing to meet
the indigenization levels could continue production after
obtaining licenses from the government for import of spare parts.
 
</P>
