<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nobel Laureates Honored In Sweden, Norway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, December 10(Xinhua)-- The 1997 Nobel prize-awarding
ceremony is held here Wednesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Some 1,800 people including the Swedish King Carl XVI Gustaf,
Parliament Speaker Birgitta Dahl, Prime Minister Goran Persson,
renowned scientists, writers as well as notable public figures and
foreign ambassadors attended the ceremony in the Stockholm concert
hall.
</P>
<P>
Professor Bengt Samuelsson, Chairman of the Nobel Prize
Foundation, made the opening speech and gave introduction of the
achievements made in science, literature and economy in the past
year.
</P>
<P>
The King awarded certificates, gold medals and prize checks to
the laureates in physics, chemistry, medicine, literature and
economy.
</P>
<P>
This year's Nobel prize amounts to 7.50 million Swedish Krona
(about one million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The physics prize goes to the Chinese American Professor Steven
Chu, Doctor William D. Phillips and French Professor Claude
Cohen-Tannoudji. The chemistry prize is shared by American
Professor Paul D Boyer, Doctor John E Walker of Britain and
Professor Jens C Skou of Denmark. The medicine prize goes to
Professor Stanley B Prusiner of America. The literature prize goes
to Italian play writer Dario Fo while American Professor Robert C
Merton and Myron S Scholes win the prize in economy.
</P>
<P>
A grand banquet is held in the City Hall by the Foundation in
honor of the winners tonight.
</P>
<P>
The International Campaign to Ban Landmines and its leader Jody
Williams won the Nobel peace prize and the ceremony was held in the
Norwegian Oslo City Hall. 
</P>
</TEXT>
