<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 11 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian rupiah closed
higher against the US dollar Wednesday as the market calmed down
following news that President Soeharto would attend the informal
ASEAN summit in Malaysia, currency dealers said.
</P>
<P>
But the stock market lost 2.2 percent as state-owned securities
houses, which had been actively buying stocks for the last four
days, ran out of investment resources, stockbrokers said today.
</P>
<P>
Currency dealers said here today that spot rupiah strengthened
to 4,380 against the dollar in the afternoon before closing at
4,410, compared with an opening of 4,350/4,380.
</P>
<P>
President Soeharto was rumored to be seriously ill Tuesday,
sending the rupiah to a historic low of 4,600.
</P>
<P>
The market received further relief after Minister/State
Secretary Moerdiono announced that President Soeharto would attend
next week's informal summit of the Association of Southeast Asian
Nations (ASEAN) in Kuala Lumpur.
</P>
<P>
Soeharto has been resting at home on doctors' advice since
returning last week from a strenuous 12-day trip that took him to
Namibia, South Africa, Canada and Saudi Arabia.
</P>
<P>
While the rupiah was stabilizing, share prices on the Jakarta
Stock Exchange dropped 2.2 percent, with the composite index down
9.559 points to close at 415.937.  
</P>
