<HEADLINE> Italy to Meet 3-percent Deficit-DDP Ratio </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Italy will meet the crucial
3-percent deficit-GDP ratio called for by the Maastricht Treaty
for entry into the European single currency at the end of the
year, a study by the employers' association Confindustria reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The improvement of the deficit-GDP ratio was achieved through
higher taxes and lower interest rates, not through a
much-hoped-for reform of public spending, Confindustria said in
the report on the country's economic picture.
</P>
<P>
Confindustria also predicted that in 1998, the ratio will dip
below 3 percent to 2.9 percent. 
