<P>
Phakdi Chomphooming, governor of Mae Hong Son province, said,
"we will not use them as our selling point," the Bangkok Post
today quoted him as saying.
</P>
<P>
His remarks followed an article in the Times of London, which
said the Karens, who had fled fighting in Myanmar, are being
exploited by Thai opportunists to draw tourists.
</P>
<P>
The Karens in question are living in several refugee camps in
the province. Tour guides often take foreign tourists there to see
the long-neck Karens.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
