<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lithuania Sees More Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Foreign investment flowing into
Lithuania has been increasing recently and by the end of last
September, the total that had entered since the country's
independence in 1991 amounted to 888.3 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Lithuanian Europe Affairs Ministry says the total foreign
investment will amount to one billion dollars by the end of this
year.
</P>
<P>
During the first nine months of this year 316 million dollars
worth of investments came into the country, while the total
investment in 1996 was 220 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
About two billion dollars of foreign money is expected to have
entered the country by the end of 1998, with the biggest investor
being the United States, followed by Sweden and Germany. 
</P>
</TEXT>
