<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Railway Line Spurs Economy in Mountainous Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, December 11 (Xinhua) -- The economic picture in
backward southwestern Baise prefecture is looking up with the
opening of the Nanning-Kunming Railway trunk line.
</P>
<P>
Located in a mountainous region of landlocked Guangxi
Autonomous Region, the area's 3.08 million residents are mainly
Zhuang, Yao, Miao and other minority people. The prefecture has
been listed as one of the 18 poor areas in the country.
</P>
<P>
However, rich mineral resources have been verified here.
Reserves of bauxite, copper, crystal and brown coal rank first in
the region.
</P>
<P>
Construction started in 1990 on the western section of the
Nanning-Kunming Railway, which stretches 272 kilometers through
Baise for 30 percent of its total length.
</P>
<P>
The railway has greatly enhanced the local economic potential
by bringing large amount of raw materials and equipment to the
region and transporting non-ferrous metals, building materials and
machinery to other regions.
</P>
<P>
The Pingguo Aluminium Plant, built shortly after the railway's
construction, has become the largest aluminium production center
in China with a capacity of 300,000 tons of aluminium oxide and
100,000 tons of electrolytic aluminium.
</P>
<P>
Agriculture along the railway has also developed
rapidly. Production centers with an area of 66,667 hectares each
have been set up for mustard greens, sugarcane, bamboo, camellia
tea, Chinese chestnuts and fruit.
</P>
<P>
Economic growth in Baise began to draw the attention of
overseas investors in 1995 with 61 foreign-funded projects along
the Nanning-Baise section of the railway with an investment of
118 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
During the last seven years, 1.24 million impoverished Baise
people have risen above the poverty line. In the first half of
this year, Baise's Gross Domestic Product increased 11.2 percent
from the same period last year. The per-capita annual income now
averages 1,435 yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
