<HEADLINE> Beijing to Host Ceramics Industrial Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 11 (Xinhua) -- A large-scale exhibition of
the ceramics industry in Asia will be held in Beijing next April,
according to today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, China International Ceramics Industry
Exhibition (Ceramics China), is co-sponsored by the Administration
of Building Materials Industry and the China National Council of
Light Industry.
</P>
<P>
Organizers of the exhibition have decided to alternate the
event in Beijing and Guangzhou every year.
</P>
<P>
Ceramics China '98, to be held between April 21 and 25 in
Beijing, will provide more than 10,000 square meters of exhibition
area.
</P>
<P>
Business representatives and industrial officials from
countries such as the United Kingdom, Italy, Germany and Japan
will participate in the event. They will also help organize their
pavilions at the show, said the organizers.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will display ceramics products and the
industry's most up-to-date machinery and technology.
</P>
<P>
China has decided to make the building materials industry one
of the five pillar industries for the development of its national
economy during the Ninth Five-Year Plan period (1996-2000).
</P>
