<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian Lira Unruffled by Fresh Asian Flutters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 10 (Xinhua) -- The Italian currency, lira, had
an untroubled day on international currency market today
despite flutters from Asia.
</P>
<P>
The South Korean won has now lost 36.5 percent since the Asian
currency crisis began a month ago, the steepest plunge of all the
Asian currencies.
</P>
<P>
The second worst performing currency is the Indonesian rupiah,
down 25.89 percent since November 10, and the third worst the Thai
baht, down more than 12 percent.
</P>
<P>
Today the Japanese yen gained against lira, at 13,563 from
13,456 yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Except for its loss to the Japanese yen, lira held strong
against other major currencies and even advanced against the
U.S. dollar, at 1,744.60 lira from 1,751.03. 
</P>
</TEXT>
