<HEADLINE> Ice And Snow Festival to Open in Harbin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, December 11 (Xinhua) -- The 14th Ice and Snow Festival
will open to tourists on Jan. 5 in Harbin, capital of northeast
China's Heilongjiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The festival, which began in 1985, has become a traditional
winter event in the city, attracting tourists from home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, about 30,000 people attended last
year's festival. An Ice and Snow Festival official said even more
people are expected to attend this year.
</P>
<P>
The festival has changed from previous years in both content
and form. The content will include not only ice carvings and snow
sculpture, but also entertainment programs and trade and economic
activities, according to the official.
</P>
<P>
The ice and snow make the city look like a crystal world. The
Children's Garden is decorated as a fairy kingdom and many works
of art are on both sides of the European-style Central Street, a
symbol of the city. More than 100 scenic spots and the winding
river through the city all take on a new look with ice ornaments.
</P>
<P>
The Zhaolin Garden, a major attraction at the festival,
contains thousands of pieces of ice carvings using 50,000 cubic
meters of ice, two times last year's amount.
</P>
<P>
The festival's 14th economic and trade fair will be held
simultaneously.
</P>
<P>
Other January activities in Harbin include the International
Conference of the Northern Cities, which will convene on the
15th.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
