<HEADLINE> Russia, Georgia to Resume Border Demarkation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Russia and Georgia have agreed
to immediately resume the work of border demarkation commissions.
</P>
<P>
Russian First Deputy Foreign Minister Boris Pastukhov was
quoted by the Interfax news agency as saying Wednesday that the
agreement was reached during Georgia's Deputy Prime Minister
Valery Serov's visit to Tbilisi on December 8-9.
</P>
<P>
Last Friday, the Georgian Foreign Ministry made a statement,
saying that Georgia would discontinue the work of the commissions
in protest of the moving of a Russian border post into Georgian
territory.
</P>
<P>
During Serov's visit, Russia agreed to move the post back to
its former position, thus setting the stage for the restarting of
the delimitation work.
</P>
<P>
But Russia insists the agreement does not mean it was wrong in
moving the post in the first place. 
