<HEADLINE> Police, Military Officers Behind Kidnappings: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 11 (Xinhua) -- A group of middle-ranking
police and military officers have been tagged by intelligence
reports as the alleged brains behind kidnap and bank robbery
syndicates operating in Metro Manila, the local press reported
today.
</P>
<P>
Appearing before a hearing of the House Committee on Public
Order and Security, Justice Secretary Teofisto Guingona said on
Wednesday that these officers are now under surveillance and would
be arrested within two weeks.
</P>
<P>
He said that the officers supplied guns, stolen vehicles, map
and mobile telephones to abductors, adding that these kidnap
groups can be classified as "the sophisticated organized groups",
armed with cellular phones and vehicles.
</P>
<P>
However, he further assured the public by saying that "not all
kidnap and bank robbery syndicates have military and police
officials as protectors."
</P>
<P>
Vice President Jose Estrada claimed earlier that more than 50
percent of the country's kidnap-for-ransom cases were undertaken
by rogue policemen and soldiers.
</P>
<P>
The government recently launched a drive against kidnappers
after the Filipino-Chinese living here staged a series of protests
against rampant kidnappings. Police said they had busted three
kidnap gangs and rounded up 28 kidnap suspects.  
</P>
