<HEADLINE> Italy's 9-Month Trade Surplus Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Italy's trade surplus fell by
more than 10 trillion lire (5.7 billion U.S. dollars) in the first
nine months of 1997, according to the national statistics bureau,
Istat.
</P>
<P>
The surplus achieved during the first nine months of 1997 was
39.4 trillion lire (around 23 billion dollars), down from 50
trillion lire (around 29 billion dollars) in the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
September 1997 showed a surplus of 1.02 trillion lire (around
570 million dollars), down almost two-thirds from the 2.82
trillion lire (around 1.6 billion dollars) surplus in September
1996.
</P>
<P>
Trade with EU countries showed a deficit of 55 billion lire in
September 1997, down from a surplus of 1.32 trillion lire (around
750 million dollars) in the same month last year. 
</P>
