<HEADLINE> Myanmar Calls for More Donation of Corneas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, December 11 (Xinhua) -- A senior Myanmar health
official has called for more donation of corneas for treatment of
people who suffer from cataracts.
</P>
<P>
Meeting with members of the Myanmar National Eye Bank Committee
here Wednesday, Minister for Health Ket Sein said there are over
20,000 blind people in the country who need corneas and 4,000
people become blind yearly due to injury, deficiency of vitamin,
trachoma and cataracts, the official newspaper The New Light of
Myanmar reported today.
</P>
<P>
Over 100 patients can be operated yearly after the
establishment of an eye bank, he said, disclosing that 1,493
corneas have been received from donors since 1993.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the need to extensively carry out health education
to attract more donation of corneas.
</P>
<P>
He also called for cooperation of non-governmental
organizations to obtain corneas.  
</P>
