<HEADLINE> Chinese Company to Invest $4 Million in Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Dalian Hua Feng
Enterprises, one of the largest private Chinese companies, will
invest 4 million U.S. dollars in Argentina to construct a
refrigeration plant.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed here Wednesday between the Dalian Hua
Feng Enterprises and its Argentine partner Carnes de San Justo.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, the Chinese company, one of the
five investors involved in the project, will receive a 10 percent
share of the venture. The other four venturers are from Argentina,
Germany, Italy and the United States.
</P>
<P>
The total investment is 150 million dollars, 40 million of
which will be provided by the five investors. The remaining 110
million will be raised by selling bonds in the United States and
Europe.
</P>
<P>
The refrigeration plant, to be located in Buenos Aires, is
scheduled to start operating in mid 1999.
</P>
<P>
Roberto Cruz, vice president of the Carnes de San Justo
company, said the plant will be equipped with state of the art
technology to meet the ISO-9000 and ISO-14000 quality guidelines
and U.S. federal government standards.
</P>
<P>
In addition, a section will be built for meat processing. The
businessmen, including the Chinese, intend to export the meat to
the United States and other countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
