<HEADLINE> Hungary's Exports Hit a High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Hungary had a trade surplus
with European Union (EU) countries in the first 10 months this
year, the first in 30 years, the Ministry of Industry and
Commerce, Tourism (MICT) announced here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Hungary's exports to EU countries in the period hit a record
high with changes in its foreign trade structure.
</P>
<P>
Exports to the 15 EU countries were worth 10.754 billion
U.S. dollars, while imports from these countries amounted to
10.616 billion U.S. dollars, leaving a surplus of 138 million
U.S. dollars. The biggest trade surplus was with Germany.
</P>
<P>
The Hungarian ministry pointed out that among exports,
processed products and machinery accounted for the biggest
proportion. Exports of farm produce, which used to be the
traditional Hungarian exports, have been reducing year by year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
