<HEADLINE> Italian Senate Gives Green Light to Single Currency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 10 (Xinhua) -- The Italian Senate today approved
the mandate to the government to introduce the euro, the European
single currency, into the Italian monetary system.
</P>
<P>
The green light came from all traditional pro-European parties
as well as Communist Refoundation which, in the past, has been
critical of the parameters imposed for monetary union.
</P>
<P>
The mandate was passed by the House on October 29 and
authorizes the government to issue legislative decrees to
incorporate European Union laws dealing with the euro.
</P>
<P>
The euro is slated to fully enter circulation in the year 2002.
</P>
