<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Province Leases Highway Operating Rights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, December 11 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Guizhou
Province has leased out partial operating rights on two sections
of its graded highways around its provincial capital of Guiyang to
a Hong Kong company.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was reached recently by Guizhou Provincial
Expressway Development Corp. and China Merchants (Hong Kong) Group
Co.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time the province has leased partial
operating rights of expressways to a commercial company. The
transfer is considered conducive to collecting funds for building
and upgrading highways.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, both sides will cooperate in the
operation of the two highway sections, which are 38.93
kilometers. The duration of the agreement is 25 years.
</P>
<P>
Asset evaluations show that the two highway sections are worth
more than 900 million yuan. The Hong Kong group will cover 60
percent of the investment, while the Guizhou company will bear the
remaining 40 percent.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the contract, the Guizhou company will list
"Merchants International" shares on 30 percent of the highways'
total assets on the Hong Kong stock exchange.
</P>
<P>
Through the leasing, the Guizhou company will pool capital of
more than 400 million yuan and control 33.28 million "Merchants
International" shares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
