<HEADLINE> Brazil's Coffee Exports Up in November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's coffee exports
reached over 190 million U.S. dollars in November, compared to
149.6 million dollars for November 1996, said the coffee
exporters' association Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The total coffee exports in the first ten months of this year
increased to 13.26 million sacks (60 kilograms each) from the
11.23 million sacks in the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
The association said that the foreign currency earned from the
exports has amounted to 2.513 billion dollars, compared to the
total 1.7 billion dollars for last year.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the association forecast that Brazil may export
nearly 1 million sacks of green coffee, which will produce 217
million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Brazil's total green coffee exports for 1997 may reach 2.730
billion dollars, a 61 percent increase over last year. 
</P>
