<HEADLINE> Argentina Keeps "Martin Fierro" Manuscript </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, December 10 (Xinhua) -- An Argentine businessman
has decided to purchase the first section of the manuscript of
the famous poem "Martin Fierro" and donate it to the National
Historic Museum, the Ministry of Culture said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Martin Fierro", written by poet Jose Hernandez, enjoys the
same position in Argentine literature as "Don Quixote" in the
literature of Spain.
</P>
<P>
The businessman, Pedro Simoncini, said his company is willing
to pay the entire cost of the poetic work and then donate it to
the nation.
</P>
<P>
His action prevents the masterpiece of Argentine literature
from being purchased by foreigners at auction and taken out of the
country. 
</P>
