<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Strengthen Management of Fire-fighting Equipment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 11 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Public
Security recently issued a notice calling on fire departments
across the nation to strengthen the supervision and management of
fire-fighting equipment.
</P>
<P>
The notice stipulates that great importance should be attached
to appraising and checking fire-fighting equipment prior to
granting approval for delivery, with facilities designated as key
projects cautioned to pay especially close attention.
</P>
<P>
Fire departments are prohibited from preventing any brand of
fire-control equipment which meets state standards from entering
local markets.
</P>
<P>
Repeated appraisals and checks involving extra charges prior to
acceptance are prohibited, according to the notice.
</P>
<P>
The ministry has pledged to gradually perfect the supervision
and management system for various types of fire-fighting equipment
as part of an effort to prevent fake low quality products from
entering the market.
</P>
<P>
The notice emphasizes that fire departments at all levels
should spare no effort to promote clean and honest operations in
order to enhance their image with the general public. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
