<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Forestry Park Expected to Improve Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, December 11 (Xinhua) -- China is establishing a
forestry park near northwest China's major coking coal producer
in Shizuishan, the Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The park, covering three sq.km., will have well over 260,000
trees representing 115 species, expansive grasslands and an
80,000-cubic meter reservoir.
</P>
<P>
Experts say the park will greatly improve the local ecological
environment, and will at the same time protect the urban area and
cultivated land from windstorms and sandstorms.
</P>
<P>
The park will also help to conserve water and improve the
quality of the atmosphere, according to experts.
</P>
<P>
Shizuishan, which is known as the "Coal City" and is one of
China's new industrial cities, is famous for its production of
high quality anthracite.
</P>
<P>
The city suffers from serious pollution resulting from
inadequate precipitation, a lack of vegetation, strong winds and
dust. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971211.0307 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Farmers Organize to Compete on Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, December 11 (Xinhua) -- A kind of newly emerging economic
organization -- farmers' associations -- are gaining popularity in
the rural areas of northwest China's Shaanxi Province. The
associations have been successful in helping farmers compete
profitably on the market.
</P>
<P>
By the end of October, the province had set up 8,192 farmers'
associations in planting, breeding, processing and transporting
activities that include 760,000 people.
</P>
<P>
By joining the organizations, farmers expect to reduce natural
and market risks. The household-based economic activity has been
considered by local farmers fragile and less competitive in the
market economy which is taking shape in rural China, said Shi
Zhicheng, director of the province's Agriculture Department.
</P>
<P>
The number of farmers' associations is increasing and, more
importantly, the organizations are also expanding their service
areas from seed supply to providing techniques, processing and
marketing support.
</P>
<P>
In Fengxiang County the Fruits Growers' Association has opened
branches in 16 townships and 40 villages. It has trained more than
10,000 farmers and helped sell 80 million kilograms of apples
during the last four years.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has adopted some measures to promote
the organizations' healthy development, Shi said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971211.0308 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hainan Introduces Helicopters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, December 11 (Xinhua) -- Hainan Island has purchased two
helicopters which will be used for medical evacuation and disaster
relief, as well as for anti-smuggling and anti-narcotics
operations.
</P>
<P>
The helicopters will also be used for ocean surveys, business
trips for government officials and short flights.
</P>
<P>
The Zhi-9 model aircraft, which has a capacity of 14 passengers,
can cruise at 314 kilometers per hour. The model is considered the
best helicopter made in China.
</P>
<P>
A French-made helicopter, with a capacity of six passengers,
has a flight speed of 290 kilometers per hour. 
</P>
</TEXT>
