<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Science Projects to Aid Poverty Alleviation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUILIN, December 11 (Xinhua) -- Science and technology projects
have helped members of minority ethnic groups living in
poverty-stricken areas in south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
Region escape poverty.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS) and local
governments jointly established a technology demonstration zone
and a technological development company to aid poverty-stricken
areas in the Huanjiang Maonan Autonomous County. The company has
allowed local farmers to move to the special technology zone, and
obtain loans of farming tools, fertilizer and seed plants, as well
as extra subsidies for living expenses in order to develop
agriculture and increase their personal income.
</P>
<P>
The company has also allocated a certain portion of profits and
taxes to construct public infrastructure, including roads,
schools, water treatment and power generation plants.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the company has provided a number of services such
as providing farmers with seedlings, marketing agricultural
products and sponsoring advanced technology training programs.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
