<HEADLINE> Argentina's Provincial Governor Visits Cuba </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, December 10 (Xinhua) -- Ramon Mestre, governor of
Argentina's province of Cordova, met Cuban officials Wednesday to
study the possibilities of closer trade cooperation, diplomatic
sources said.
</P>
<P>
Mestre reviewed business opportunities with Raul Taladrid,
Cuba's Under Minister of Foreign Investment and Economic
Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
At a separate meeting with Cuba's Under Minister of Tourism
Miguel Brugueras, Mestre said he was aware that the South American
market is considered one of Cuba's most important tourism markets.
</P>
<P>
Brugueras gave an overview of the Cuban tourism industry which
attracted over 1 million visitors for the second straight year and
is the most dynamic sector of that island nation's economy.
</P>
<P>
Tourists who come to Cuba are mainly from Italy, Canada, Spain,
France, Germany and Mexico.
</P>
<P>
Mestre will visit duty-free zone Havana In Bond and meet
Conrado Martinez Corona, president of the Provincial Assembly of
Popular Power in the city of Havana. 
</P>
