<HEADLINE> Unemployment Rate Up in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, December 10 (Xinhua) -- The unemployment rate for
Brazil in October reached 5.71 percent, up 0.8 percent over
September, reported the Brazilian Institute of Geography and
Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The institute added that this figure is an increase of 0.57
percent over October 1996.
</P>
<P>
Unemployment is growing in all sectors, especially industry,
construction and services.
</P>
<P>
At the end of 1996, the country's unemployment rate was 5.4
percent.
</P>
<P>
The government is concerned by the upward trend of unemployment
for in the last 15 years the average annual employment rate was
4.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Brazil has a population of around 160 million, 70 million of
them are involved in labor. 
</P>
</TEXT>
