<HEADLINE> Shanxi's First Public Property Auction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, December 11 (Xinhua) -- The Taiyuan Auction Company in
north China's Shanxi Province recently auctioned public property
valued at over three million yuan (361,000 US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The auction was the first such kind since the province
introduced the sale of public property earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
Public property involved includes goods confiscated by
industrial, commercial and taxation departments, as well as goods
confiscated by courts and overstocked products of enterprises such
as automobiles, machinery, textile products, garments, daily-use
goods and electric appliances.
</P>
<P>
Only 70,000 yuan worth of goods were sold due to the lack of
promotion and people's declining interest in purchasing outdated
products.  
</P>
