<HEADLINE> Dow Continues to Slide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, December 10 (Xinhua) -- New York stocks fell today,
sending the Dow industrials below 8,000 again, brought down by a
continuing slide in technology shares.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average, at one point down nearly 111
points, was off 70.87 points, closing at 7,978.79.
</P>
<P>
The Dow still is up more than 23 percent so far this year.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by nearly 2 to 1 on the
New York Stock Exchange, where volume totaled 482.41 million
shares as against 436.53 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
Broader indexes also were lower, especially in the
technology-laden Nasdaq Stock Market.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list fell 9.73 to 966.05, and
the NYSE composite index fell 5.28 at 505.58.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index declined 30.51 to 1,590.04, and the
American Stock Exchange composite index lost 3.2 to 668.34.
