<HEADLINE> IDB Okays 100 Mln Dlrs for Road Improvement in Colombia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 10 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) today announced the approval of a 100
million U.S. dollar loan to Colombia to help upgrade its road
network.
</P>
<P>
The project is designed to rehabilitate, upgrade, and maintain
the main departmental roads, reducing transportation cost. The
capacity of the departments to plan and modernize the road system
under their jurisdictions will be strengthened.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the program is some 167 million dollars.
Apart from the IDB loan, which is payable for a 20-year term, with
a four-year grace period, local counterpart funds total 67 million
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Loans to Colombia this year total some 225 million dollars,
supporting investments in areas such as land titling, fiscal
reform, energy and road construction. The IDB has also approved
31.5 million dollar risk guarantee this year for a private sector
project in Colombia, the first such guarantee by the Bank.
</P>
</TEXT>
