<HEADLINE> IDB Approves 412 Mln Dlrs for Two Projects in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 10 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) today announced the approval of 412 million
U.S. dollars in financing for two private projects in Brazil.
</P>
<P>
Of the two projects, ITA Energetica, S.A. will receive some 375
million dollars in financing for the construction, operation and
maintenance of a hydroelectric project in southern Brazil with the
installed capacity of 1,450 MW.
</P>
<P>
The IDB financing consists of a 75 million dollar loan from its
ordinary capital and a syndicated loan of 300 million dollars with
funds provided by commercial banks.
</P>
<P>
The project will be located on the Uruguai River on the border
between the states of Santa Catarina and Rio Grande do Sul.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the project is some 1,070 million dollars.
Banco Nacional de Desnvolvimento Economico e Social is providing a
significant portion of the debt financing.
</P>
<P>
For the other project, 38 million dollars in IDB financing will
support the expansion, operation and maintenance of a 60-km toll
road connecting Rio Bonito, Araruama and Sao Pedro da Aldeia in
the Region dos Lagos in the state of Rio de Janeiro.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the project is 80 million dollars. The IDB
financing consists of an 18 million dollar loan from ordinary
capital and a syndicated loan of 19 million dollars for commercial
banks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
